      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add auto fast mode cutoff",
        "body": "Fixes #85087\n\n## Summary\n\n- adds `fast: auto` alongside `fast: on/off`, with the default 60s cutoff and configurable `fast_seconds` plumbing\n- switches provider/app-server fast handling to a dynamic resolver so retries/continuations after the cutoff run without priority/fast tier where the backend can retier\n- emits channel-visible fast progress notices for long turns: `💨Fast: auto-off(...)` mid-turn and `💨Fast: auto-on` after reset\n- updates TUI/UI/ACP/protocol/docs/tests for the new auto mode\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `node scripts/format-docs.mjs --check`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/check-changed.mjs`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm --config.verify-deps-before-run=false build`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/openai-stream-wrappers.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/minimax-stream-wrappers.test.ts extensions/anthropic/stream-wrappers.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/extra-params.sampling.test.ts src/acp/translator.session-rate-limit.test.ts src/agents/fast-mode.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/xai/stream.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.media-only.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts src/tui/commands.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts -t \"re-resolves automatic OpenClaw fast mode\"`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/protocol/index.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-directives.target-session.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.media-only.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run.fast-mode-auto.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts -t \"fast auto progress\"`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `fast: auto` starts with effective fast mode enabled, flips later runtime model calls off after the configured threshold, emits channel-visible `💨Fast: auto-off(...)`, and resets with `💨Fast: auto-on` at turn end. Codex app-server cannot retier a single already-started app-server call mid-request; the targeted app-server test asserts the resolver is called only for resume and turn/start, not again while that turn is in flight.\n\nReal environment tested: local managed Gateway LaunchAgent, CLI/Gateway `2026.5.20`, Telegram plugin enabled/configured/running/connected in polling mode, redacted bound Telegram DM session, real provider `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` through Codex app-server.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\npnpm --config.verify-deps-before-run=false build\npnpm --config.verify-deps-before-run=false openclaw gateway restart\npnpm --config.verify-deps-before-run=false openclaw gateway status --deep\npnpm --config.verify-deps-before-run=false openclaw channels status --deep --channel telegram\npnpm --config.verify-deps-before-run=false openclaw gateway call chat.send --json --params '{\n  \"sessionKey\":\"<redacted telegram direct session>\",\n  \"message\":\"Before replying, run a shell command exactly: sleep 3; echo fast-auto-2s-proof. After the command finishes, reply exactly: fast-auto-2s-proof complete\",\n  \"fastMode\":\"auto\",\n  \"fast_seconds\":2,\n  \"deliver\":true,\n  \"timeoutMs\":180000,\n  \"idempotencyKey\":\"fast-auto-2s-live-20260522050008\"\n}'\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: redacted proof screenshot: https://files.catbox.moe/ljignx.png; redacted HTML proof artifact: https://files.catbox.moe/3l0a3z.html. The live Computer Use Telegram view showed the channel sequence `💨Fast: auto-off(5s>2s)`, `fast-auto-2s-proof complete`, then `💨Fast: auto-on`; the elapsed value is larger than the deterministic `3s>2s` unit case because the real Codex app-server first call itself took several seconds before the 3s tool-result continuation.\n\nObserved result after fix: trajectory recorded run `fast-auto-2s-live-20260522050008`, provider `openai-codex/gpt-5.5`, `bash` tool call `sleep 3; echo fast-auto-2s-proof`, tool result duration `2962ms`, output `fast-auto-2s-proof`, a second model call after the cutoff, Telegram message-tool success `messageId=137`, and final text `fast-auto-2s-proof complete`. Gateway status probe was ok and Telegram status was connected before the live run.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad changed-suite/Testbox proof was not completed locally for this XL cross-surface feature. Exporting the literal Telegram window screenshot through shell/Peekaboo was blocked by macOS Screen Recording TCC, so the attached public artifact is a redacted proof sheet generated from local trajectory plus Computer Use observation rather than a raw chat-window capture.\n",
